<subSubSection pageNumber="569" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="569">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">Note:</emphasis>
Burtt &amp; Lewis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">Kew Bull.</emphasis>
7: 337-338. 1952) argued that although 312.5 (LINN) is identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Cressa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">Cressa cretica</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Convolvulaceae</taxonomicName>
), it is not original material for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Herniaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lenticulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">H. lenticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which should be based instead on material in 
<specimenReference collectionCode="BAS">
Herb. Bauhin (
<collectionCode>BAS</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
. This, too, would not be original material but Burtt &amp; Lewis declined to make any formal type choice. Chaudhri (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">Rev. Paronychiinae</emphasis>
: 398. 1968), however, excluded this name from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Herniaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">Herniaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and treated it as a synonym of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="569">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Cressa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">Cressa cretica</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In the absence of original material, this synonymy is formalised by the designation of 312.5 (LINN) as a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
